'''Plati''' ({{lang-el|<U+03A0><U+03BB><U+03AC><U+03C4><U+03B7>}}) is a village in the northern part of the [[Evros (regional unit)|Evros regional unit]] in Greece. It is part of the municipal unit [[Trigono]]. In 2001 its population was 601. Plati is located on the left bank of the river [[Arda (Maritsa)|Ardas]], between the villages [[Elaia, Evros|Elaia]] to the west and [[Arzos]] to the east.

